{"name":"Devotional Iconography","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Devotional iconography takes many forms, including sanctified scrolls, purity seals, large metal halos, and even entire suits of armour covered in barely visible micro-etching.</p>\n<p>Effect: The wearer gains a +10 bonus to Command tests when dealing with those faithful to the Imperium, but sufers a &ndash;10 penalty to Fellowship tests when dealing with those not loyal to the Emperor.</p>","availability":"common","weight":1,"upgrades":"Any armour","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0BLKNKsFkt9drVhb"}
{"name":"Sacred Incense Burner","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Filled with blessed herbs and spices, a sacred incense burner sends billowing clouds of strong-smelling smoke in all directions. Daemons find the holy odours repulsive, leaving them weakened and disoriented.</p>\n<p>Effect: A sacred incense burner must be affixed to a backpack, helmet, or similarly worn item. Setting it aflame requires a Half Action and it can burn for 1 hour. While the burner is alight, any creature with the Daemonic trait within 3 metres of the bearer suffers a &ndash;10 penalty to Weapon Skill tests and a &ndash;10 penalty to Warp Instability tests.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":3,"upgrades":"Any armour","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0dIaLwH8nReAKmZE"}
{"name":"Mono","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Mono weapons have extraordinarily sharp edges, making each blade an even greater threat. Melee weapons without an actual edge, such as mauls or hammers, can also use this upgrade; for these weapons the effect can be due to pneumo-shocks, inertial multipliers, or some other more fitting enhancement. A weapon with this modification loses the Primitive quality (if it had it) and has its penetration increased by 2. This upgrade can be applied to a power weapon, but it has no effect whilst the power field is active. If the power field is ever lost or deactivated, the mono upgrade&rsquo;s bonuses then apply.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any Low-Tech or Power Melee weapon","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1KL3VLC6RbIwTRr0"}
{"name":"Sacred Inscriptions","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The character inscribes a sacred script from the Imperial Creed upon the weapon. These inscriptions are generally etched into the weapon&rsquo;s surface and might be lavishly illuminated with valuable metals, jewels, and embedded relics, medals, or talismans from members of the Ecclesiarchy. The constant reminder of his faith serves to instil additional courage in the weapon&rsquo;s wielder when his courage is tested. A character who possesses one or more weapons with this modification gains a +10 bonus to Pinning tests.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any Weapon","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1swwlQAAx82ZJH0j"}
{"name":"Auxiliary Grenade Launcher","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A small, single-shot version of the regular grenade launcher is fitted onto another ranged weapon such as a lasgun, allowing the user to fire a single grenade instead of firing as normal, and adding 2.5 kg to the weapon&rsquo;s weight. A character using a weapon with an auxiliary grenade launcher can choose to either fire the launcher or the weapon it is attached to in his turn, but not both at once. It has a range of 45 metres with damage and penetration as per the loaded grenade, and can be fired Indirectly. The device however is too cumbersome to be reloaded during combat; each new acquisition for the weapon reloads the launcher with one fresh round but does not require the modification to be reapplied.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":2.5,"upgrades":"Any Las, Solid Projectile, or Bolt weapons of the Basic class","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3KnQkwfG0OZB87Vm"}
{"name":"Adamantine Chainguard","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Some devoted Imperial servants wrap their armour in heavy links, the added weight acting as a reminder of the burdens Mankind must shoulder on the path to righteousness. The chains also act as a secondary defensive measure, breaking weapons that strike them. <br />Effect: When an enemy uses a melee weapon to strike a character wearing this armour, if the 1s digit of his attack roll is a 1, the weapon is destroyed unless it has the Power Field or Warp Weapon quality, or is otherwise immune to being destroyed (such as being granted by the Natural Weapons trait). This upgrade imposes a &ndash;5 penalty on the upgraded armour&rsquo;s Maximum Agility rating due to its bulk.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":4,"upgrades":"Any armour","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4Zoi1iRmDjrotR1P"}
{"name":"Pentagramatic Wards","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>One of the Ordo Malleus&rsquo;s most closely guarded secrets, these wards come about through a complex and arcane process of occult rituals, holy symbology, and the application of lost aerythmetical formulae. When complete, pentagramatic wards block Warp entities, and are often so potent that even approaching one is enough to damage or banish a Daemon.</p>\n<p>Effect: Whenever a character with the Daemonic or Warp Instability trait becomes engaged in melee with the warded armour&rsquo;s wearer or begins his turn engaged with the wearer, that character must make a Hard (&ndash;20) Willpower test. If the character fails, he suffers 1d5 Energy damage per degree of failure (ignoring armour and Toughness bonus). If the character scores 4 or more degrees of success on the test, however, the pentagramatic ward shatters and the armour permanently loses this upgrade.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any armour.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4xBzfXbBzVfO7hj7"}
{"name":"Preysense Sight","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A gun can only have one sight.</p>\n<p>This device shows thermal images and reveals the hiding places of enemies who lurk in the darkness. A character using a preysense sight suffers no penalties due to darkness and gains a +20 bonus to vision-based Perception tests in the dark.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":0.5,"upgrades":"Any ranged Las, Solid Projectile, Bolt, Low-Tech, or Plasma weapon of the Basic class","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"5KMJqZfDBBmtUCie"}
{"name":"Brazier of Saint Roberto","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A common item among Ecclesiarchy priests, Sisters of Battle, and devoted Inquisitors of the Ordo Hereticus, braziers serve little practical purpose, but act as beacons of inspiration for the faithful. Most Askellian braziers include the iconography of Saint Roberto&mdash;a martyred priest said to have faced down an army of mutants with nothing but a knife and his faith&mdash;and feature either his holy seal or a representation of his blade.</p>\n<p>Effect: A brazier must be aixed to a backpack, helmet, or similarly worn item. Setting it aflame requires a Half Action and it can burn for 2 hours. Whilst alight, it acts as a glow-globe and grants a +30 bonus to all Charm and Command tests, a +10 bonus to Intimidate tests, and a &ndash;40 penalty to all Stealth tests. If the wearer is ever knocked Prone while it is lit, he must pass an Ordinary (+10) Agility test to avoid setting himself on fire.</p>","availability":"common","weight":10,"upgrades":"Any armour, helmet, or backpack","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8yTUSm14bUdPHuo3"}
{"name":"Tox Dispenser","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The custom of lining a blade with deadly toxins has been with humanity since the dawn of recorded time. Although smearing a poison on the blade has the advantage of simplicity, technology has since provided a better solution. A series of micro-dispensers allow a wielder to coat his weapon with poisons by simply pushing a button. As a Free Action, a character with a weapon equipped with a tox dispenser may cause his weapon to gain the Toxic (2) quality for one round. A tox dispenser can be used 10 times before requiring refilling; no Requisition test in needed as long as the character is in a location the ingredients would be available.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":0.75,"upgrades":"Any Low-Tech or Chain melee weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9Z69KgUIGxwozGJ8"}
{"name":"Truesilver Gilding","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Weapons with Truesilver gilding have an inexplicable sturdiness in the face of unnatural foes, almost as if the mere presence of the sanctified silver was enough to turn aside ensorcelled blades and deflect daemonic talons.</p>\n<p>Effect: A weapon with Truesilver gilding grants its wielder a bonus to tests to Parry the attacks of foes with the Daemonic trait equal to 5 times the wielder&rsquo;s Willpower bonus.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any Low-Tech melee weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FU6ZKSN2sOUYI2eU"}
{"name":"Pistol Grip","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This modified handle is designed for smoother usage, and allows the weapon to be wielded in one hand without the usual &ndash;20 penalty. However, it becomes more difficult to aim accurately and thus its range is halved.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any Basic ranged weapon","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GkevkmWnNXlwsuQX"}
{"name":"Quick-Release","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This customisation can encompass blessed lubricant oils, extra clips mounted along the stock, revered ejection springs recovered from ancient weapons, and more, all designed to create more time shooting and less time reloading. The weapon&rsquo;s reload time is reduced by a Half Action, down to a minimum of a Half Action. For example, a weapon that normally took 2 Full Actions to reload can be reloaded with one Full Action and one Half Action.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any ranged weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"His0BDGP5NIeSvl3"}
{"name":"Vox-Operated","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Keyed into the user&rsquo;s vocal signature, these vox receptors are linked into a weapon&rsquo;s firing controls. With spoken commands, the operator can fire his gun, switch firing modes, and also change ammunition (should it be fitted with a fire selector).</p>","availability":"rare","weight":0.5,"upgrades":"Any Pistol, Basic, Launcher, or Heavy weapon that is not of the Low-Tech type.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JkkEmks6nm4fkB3B"}
{"name":"Targeter","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Heavy and precious, targeters are highly valuable devices that use a combination of guidance cogitators and sensors to improve accuracy. They are often linked directly into a gun&rsquo;s machine spirit, and allow a greater bond between wielder and weapon. If there is a final penalty to a Ballistic Skill test when using a weapon with a targeter, it is reduced by ten. Thus, a Very Hard (&ndash;30) final penalty to hit becomes Hard (&ndash;20) for example.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":1.5,"upgrades":"Any Las, Solid Projectile, Bolt, or Heavy weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KRlItkBVaS5CyBrI"}
{"name":"Reinforced","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Weight: +20%</p>\n<p>Most combat veterans know that no matter their ranged skill, there are always occasions where the enemy closes and there is no time to reload. A suitably modified gun can be a surprisingly effective weapon in these situations, and turn a charging heretic into the makings for new CS Rations. A weapon&rsquo;s weight is increased by 20% when it becomes reinforced. If it is a ranged weapon, it receives an additional +1 bonus to damage when used as an improvised weapon. A melee weapon with this upgrade is only destroyed on a result of 41 or higher when Parried by a weapon with the Power Field quality.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":null,"upgrades":"Any Weapon","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MWZar5NVomUIkTKu"}
{"name":"Telescopic Sight","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A gun can only have one sight.</p>\n<p>This sight magnifies images, allowing the user to better target enemies at greater distances, and is a common upgrade when precision shots are needed. A weapon with a telescopic sight ignores penalties for Long and Extreme range, as long as the shooter is benefitting from a Full Action to Aim.</p>","availability":"average","weight":1,"upgrades":"Any Las, Solid Projectile, Bolt, Low-Tech or Plasma weapon of the Basic class.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Qa9ouuRLk8cCZV7X"}
{"name":"Suspensors","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Weight: x0,5</p>\n<p>Suspensors are similar to the grav plating on voidships, but instead act to lighten loads. Weapons fitted with such a wondrous technology are much easier to operate, but are so valuable that often they are salvaged before the weapon itself. Suspensors reduce the weight of a weapon by one-half. When firing a weapon with suspensors, the operator counts as having the Auto- tabilised trait and so always counts as being braced.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":null,"upgrades":"Any Heavy weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"R0UFcq99EEZ8eY8d"}
{"name":"Custom Grip","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Though minor, altering the weapon&rsquo;s grip to perfectly match its owner&rsquo;s hand can make the weapon feel like a literal extension of his arm. This alteration can be done for either the user&rsquo;s actual hand, or to match a certain glove or armour he wears, or even a special gripping action that the owner has made part of his attack style. As a consequence of these changes, the character for whom the customisation was performed receives a +5 to Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill when wielding the weapon. Other characters wielding the weapon suffer a &ndash;5 penalty, as the weapon feels slightly out of alignment when they attempt to use it.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Ri0dmaKg9HTPVeVK"}
{"name":"Auto-Senses","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Consisting of a complicated array of sensors and scanners networked into the user&rsquo;s helmet, Auto-Senses both aid in tracking targets and detecting ambushing foes.</p>\n<p>Effect: As long as the user wears the upgraded helmet, the wearer gains a +5 bonus to his Ballistic Skill and a +10 bonus to all Awareness tests based on Sight and Hearing.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":2,"upgrades":"Power armour","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Sz8DKXHOSXL7hTPj"}
{"name":"Unguents of Warding","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Unguents of Warding grant the bearer robust protection against Warp entities and psychic attacks, but take considerable time and skill to apply.</p>\n<p>Effect: Working the unguents onto armour takes roughly one hour, and empties one container for each hit location treated. As part of the process, careful rituals must also be performed to inscribe runes and litanies into the armour. This requires a Hard (&ndash;20) Scholastic Lore (Occult) or Forbidden Lore (Imperial Creed) test for each location; failure means the unguents must be cleaned off that location and the ritual started again. For each hit location treated with Unguents of Warding, the armour grants its wearer a +5 bonus to tests to resist Fear caused by characters with the Daemonic trait and to resist psychic powers. The effects of the unguents last for one month (or less due to wear and tear or contamination, at the GM&rsquo;s discretion).</p>","availability":"common","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any armour.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"T0UvRQbENj9EbvmF"}
{"name":"Motion Predictor","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The powerful cogitator within this device processes movement, and when the weapon is fired the machine spirit uses this data to follow its prey with a long, accurate burst. A motion predictor adds a +10 bonus to any Ballistic Skill test made as part of a Semi-Auto Burst or Full Auto Burst action.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":0.5,"upgrades":"Any ranged weapon (except Low-Tech) capable of Semi-Auto or Full Auto fire.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Uxe0YXvSPBVdpBep"}
{"name":"Forearm Weapon Mounting","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This heavy bracing allows a single ranged weapon to be mounted along the arm, with specific hand movements triggering the weapon. It allows the user to keep both hands free and can have a strong visual impression on their foes, as fire seems to appear from the user&rsquo;s outstretched arms. This upgrade reduces the weapon&rsquo;s range by one-third.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":1,"upgrades":"Any Las, Low-Tech, Solid Projectile, Bolt, or Melta weapon of the Pistol class.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WXV1CQUlqqtpGMr6"}
{"name":"Modified Stock","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>When the character holds a weapon with a modified stock up to aim, its contours perfectly align to his form. As the character takes aim with the weapon, it feels like a natural extension of his arms. When a character takes an Aim action with weapons modified in this way, he receives an additional +2 bonus on a Half Action or an additional +4 bonus for a Full Action. This customisation is compatible with any other devices that modify Aim actions. It is most commonly applied to the stock of a Basic ranged weapon, but comparable changes can be made to virtually any weapon.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WcRhSy3y3HqXhMXc"}
{"name":"Hexagrammatic Wards","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This upgrade uses powerful wards and a latticework of nullcircuitry to protect not just the wearer&rsquo;s body, but also his soul.</p>\n<p>Effect: The wearer gains a +20 bonus to tests made to resist any psychic attack or manipulation directed at him. The upgraded armour&rsquo;s Armour points are doubled against hits inlicted by psychic attacks. The Warp Weapon quality does not ignore the AP provided by this armour.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Carapace and power armour","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Wxv4V56a3RCUWoXa"}
{"name":"Melee Attachment","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Millennia of combat have shown the worth of a bayonet and other close combat attachments, as often foes can close before a more powerful melee weapon can be drawn. The ranged weapon counts as a spear when used in melee combat.</p>","availability":"plentiful","weight":2,"upgrades":"Any Basic ranged weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cXFbwuSWglPMt34e"}
{"name":"Photo Sight","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A gun can only have one sight.</p>\n<p>This sight reveals enemies lurking in the night, using wavelengths human eyes cannot detect. A character using a photo sight suffers no penalties due to darkness.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":0.5,"upgrades":"Any ranged Las, Solid Projectile, Bolt, Low-Tech, or Plasma weapon of the Basic class","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"d72tXA9yXnoMik9c"}
{"name":"Backpack Ammo Supply","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The weapon is fed from a backpack supply, which flows ammunition along fuel lines, power cables, or linked shells to the weapon. Though the user can now fire much longer, its more cumbersome form means reloading must wait until the combat is concluded. This increases the clip size of the weapon to five times its current clip size, but it cannot be reloaded in combat. To reload the weapon, the character must have the necessary amount of ammunition and spend five minutes reloading the backpack. If the weapon jams, it only loses one clip&rsquo;s worth of ammunition and does not need to be reloaded.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":15,"upgrades":"Any Bolt, Flame, Las, Melta, Plasma, and Solid Projectile weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"eYG1b7Xaf1WKrCbB"}
{"name":"Truesilver Filigree","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Woven through armour, Truesilver filigree is much more than decoration. Light that reflects off of the artful carvings can cause Daemons to flinch, opening them up to crippling counterattacks.</p>\n<p>Effect: While engaged in melee with the wearer of Truesilverfilagreed armor, any character with the Daemonic trait suffers a penalty to Weapon Skill tests equal to 5 times the wearer&rsquo;s Willpower bonus.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any armour.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fytcnX0OwkYfa1Ab"}
{"name":"Warpleech Canister","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A warpleech canister coats each expended round with a liquid of unknown origin, giving each shot added potency against the Daemons of Chaos. Some believe the liquid comes from the distilled blood of the exorcised, whereas others postulate more sinister origins.</p>\n<p>Effect: A weapon with this upgrade gains the Crippling (2) quality against targets with the Daemonic trait. Each canister contains enough liquid to last for 40 rounds.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":1,"upgrades":"Any Solid Projectile weapon without a silencer.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jT2rrfinOy1LDP3f"}
{"name":"Exterminator","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Many of the more zealous religious warriors of the Imperium use an exterminator cartridge on their regular weapons. This small device contains a small one-shot device that shoots out a sheet of fire. Rather than firing the weapon as normal, the wielder may discharge the exterminator cartridge as a Half Action, resolving the effects as if he had made a Standard Attack action with a flamer.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"common","weight":1,"upgrades":"Any weapon except Pistol or Thrown.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jYwLXaLauISILzUZ"}
{"name":"Ceramite Plating","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Ceramite protects against heat-based attacks, granting the wearer greater levels of protection against those who would turn fire against him.</p>\n<p>Effect: Armour upgraded with ceramite plating provides an additional 3 Armour points of protection against attacks with the Flame or Melta qualities and other heat-based attacks.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":2,"upgrades":"Carapace and power armour","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/armor-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"kyvhhY58ZwWWBzs0"}
{"name":"Silencer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>These upgrades use sonic bafflers, blessed coolant oils, and other methods to muffle the weapon&rsquo;s discharge noise, preventing detection from nearby foes. Awareness tests to hear shots made with a silenced weapon suffer an additional &ndash;20 penalty, and can only be attempted at half the normal distance.</p>","availability":"plentiful","weight":0.5,"upgrades":"Any Solid Projectile weapon of the Basic or Pistol class","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"l02SwkZRXqwwkiFK"}
{"name":"Fire Selector","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>An ideal upgrade for those using weapons that can take multiple types of ammunition, this device allows the user to swap types without needing to reload the weapon. The weapon can now have up to three different types of ammunition loaded (the total amount of shells not exceeding its clip size); at the start of his turn, the wielder can use the fire selector to select which type of ammunition he fires for his shooting that round.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"rare","weight":1,"upgrades":"Any Bolt, Launcher, and Solid Projectile weapon of the Pistol or Basic class.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oA0KBmFKcP6ZfjW1"}
{"name":"Fluid Action","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The weapon&rsquo;s internal mechanisms have been thoroughly lubricated and carefully maintained down to the finest detail. When the character uses the weapon as part of a successful Semi-Auto Burst action, he counts as scoring one additional degree of success for purposes of determining the number of rounds that hit the target. Weapons with this customisation are trickier to load, as the ammunition feed must be more carefully engaged, and so reload time is increased by an additional Half Action.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any ranged weapon capable of Semi-Automatic fire.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ptkiAm797moXpWPZ"}
{"name":"Deactivated Safety Features","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The weapon has been modified so that its volatile nature is always at the forefront, and is always ready to be fired or wielded in an instant. When using a Ready action to prepare a weapon with this modification, a character may Ready another weapon or draw another item as part of the same action. However, any time a character who is carrying a weapon with this modification suffers four or more degrees of failure on a Movement skill test, this weapon fires, activates, or cuts itself free as a result of the jostling.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any Weapon","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"s4FawdCc1AVLeTCO"}
{"name":"Omni-Scope","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>An omni-scope counts as a sight, and a gun can only have one sight.</p>\n<p>A vastly expensive and rare device normally found only in the hands of legendary assassins or bounty hunters, the omni-scope is a cluster of finely-tuned sensor wands linked to a precision lens. Some of these scopes plug directly into a bionic cranial port, allowing the user to shoot around corners without exposing himself&mdash;the scope becomes a &ldquo;third eye.&rdquo; The omni-scope combines the benefits of a preysense sight, red-dot laser sight, and telescopic sight.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":2,"upgrades":"Any Las, Solid Projectile, Bolt, Low-Tech, or Plasma weapon of the Basic class","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sIZHm5Pwr8my8KIT"}
{"name":"Tripod/Bipod","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>These attachments are for heavier weapons, or those using integral ammunition canisters rather than a backpack-mounted source (as plasma guns or meltaguns sometimes do). Resting the weapon on the ground increases accuracy but sacrifices mobility, thus making them more common in static defence lines. Bipods and tripods allow a weapon to be braced anywhere there is a reasonably flat surface. A weapon braced on a bipod has a 90&deg; fire arc, while one on a tripod has a 180&deg; arc.</p>","availability":"average","weight":2,"upgrades":"Any Basic or Heavy weapon","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tY1iiXgui27XGNT1"}
{"name":"Truesilver Weaving","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>More costly and time-consuming than the more traditional uses for Truesilver, some artisans thread tiny strands of Truesilver across the surface of bullets, quarrels, and even some explosives. The amount used is insignificant, but the effects on the daemonic can be quite dramatic.</p>\n<p>Effect: Truesilver weaving does not upgrade the weapon, but the ammunition the weapon uses. The modification requires a skilled artisan and upgrades one clip at a time. Whenever a target with the Daemonic trait attempts to Dodge an attack made with a weapon using ammunition upgraded with Truesilver weaving, the target suffers a penalty to the Dodge test equal to 5 times the attacker&rsquo;s Willpower bonus.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any Launcher, Low-Tech, or Solid Projectile ranged weapon.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uDIFY1ajoCDnWdHw"}
{"name":"Red-Dot Laser Sight","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A gun may only have one sight.</p>\n<p>This small, crimson laser sight is common on many guns, where it aids in both targeting and intimidating foe. It grants a +10 bonus to Ballistic Skill tests when firing a single shot.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":0.5,"upgrades":"Any Las, Solid Projectile, Bolt, Low-Tech, or Plasma weapon of the Pistol or Basic class","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wcuiMahfjFJKsPF6"}
{"name":"Compact","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Weight: x0,5</p>\n<p>This upgrade is ideal in stealth missions, when concealing a weapon is more important than its lethality. This halves the weight of the weapon, but also halves its clip size and range as well as reducing the inflicted damage by 1. Anyone attempting to find a concealed weapon with the Compact upgrade suffers a &ndash;20 penalty to any related Skill test (e.g., Awareness, Scrutiny). If this upgrade is forcibly removed the weapon remains smaller, but its range and clip size are reduced by half again, and its damage is reduced by 2.</p>","availability":"average","weight":0,"upgrades":"Any Pistol or any Las, Solid Projectile, Flame, Bolt, or Plasma weapon of the Basic class.","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wgEkkJyPFYchUuQ0"}
{"name":"Expanded Magazine","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weaponModification","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The ammunition storage device, such as drum cartridge or plasma flask, is increased, thus lessening the need to reload during a battle. The clip size of the weapon increases by half its current clip size (rounded up), and thus must be reloaded using ammunition/energy from multiple standard clips to fully stock the larger magazine.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":1,"upgrades":"Ranged weapons","installed":false},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WeaponAndArmorMods/weapon-upgrade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zCX5kjfJVWkDSF45"}
